{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:psalms.105",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 105,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 105 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.105.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:1",
      "text": "Give glory to the Lord, for he is good: for his mercy endureth for ever.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.105.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:2",
      "text": "Who shall declare the powers of the Lord? who shall set forth all his praises?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.105.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:3",
      "text": "Blessed are they that keep judgment, and do justice at all times.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.105.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:4",
      "text": "Remember us, O Lord, in the favour of thy people: visit us with thy salvation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.105.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:5",
      "text": "That we may see the good of thy chosen, that we may rejoice in the joy of thy nation: that thou mayst be praised with thy inheritance.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.105.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:6",
      "text": "We have sinned with our fathers: we have acted unjustly, we have wrought iniquity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.105.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:7",
      "text": "Our fathers understood not thy wonders in Egypt: they remembered not the multitude of thy mercies: And they provoked to wrath going up to the sea, even the Red Sea.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.105.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:8",
      "text": "And he saved them for his own name's sake: that he might make his power known.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.105.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:9",
      "text": "And he rebuked the Red Sea and it was dried up: and he led them through the depths, as in a wilderness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.105.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:10",
      "text": "And he saved them from the hand of them that hated them: and he redeemed them from the hand of the enemy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.105.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:11",
      "text": "And the water covered them that afflicted them: there was not one of them left.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.105.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:12",
      "text": "And they believed his words: and they sang his praises.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.105.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:13",
      "text": "They had quickly done, they forgot his works: and they waited not for his counsel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.105.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:14",
      "text": "And they coveted their desire in the desert: and they tempted God in the place without water.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.105.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:15",
      "text": "And he gave them their request: and sent fulness into their souls.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.105.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:16",
      "text": "And they provoked Moses in the camp, Aaron the holy one of the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.105.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:17",
      "text": "The earth opened and swallowed up Dathan: and covered the congregation of Abiron.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.105.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:18",
      "text": "And a fire was kindled in their congregation: the flame burned the wicked.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.105.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:19",
      "text": "They made also a calf in Horeb: and they adored the graven thing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.105.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:20",
      "text": "And they changed their glory into the likeness of a calf that eateth grass.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.105.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:21",
      "text": "They forgot God, who saved them, who had done great things in Egypt,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.105.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:22",
      "text": "Wondrous works in the land of Cham: terrible things in the Red Sea.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.105.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:23",
      "text": "And he said that he would destroy them: had not Moses his chosen stood before him in the breach: To turn away his wrath, lest he should destroy them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.105.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:24",
      "text": "And they set at nought the desirable land. They believed not his word,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.105.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:25",
      "text": "And they murmured in their tents: they hearkened not to the voice of the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.105.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:26",
      "text": "And he lifted up his hand over them: to overthrow them in the desert;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.105.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:27",
      "text": "And to cast down their seed among the nations, and to scatter them in the countries.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.105.28",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:28",
      "text": "They also were initiated to Beelphegor: and ate the sacrifices of the dead.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.105.29",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:29",
      "text": "And they provoked him with their inventions: and destruction was multiplied among them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.105.30",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:30",
      "text": "Then Phinees stood up, and pacified him: and the slaughter ceased.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.105.31",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:31",
      "text": "And it was reputed to him unto justice, to generation and generation for evermore.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.105.32",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:32",
      "text": "They provoked him also at the waters of contradiction: and Moses was afflicted for their sakes:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.105.33",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:33",
      "text": "Because they exasperated his spirit. And he distinguished with his lips.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.105.34",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:34",
      "text": "They did not destroy the nations of which the Lord spoke unto them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.105.35",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:35",
      "text": "And they were mingled among the heathens, and learned their works:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.105.36",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:36",
      "text": "And served their idols, and it became a stumblingblock to them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.105.37",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:37",
      "text": "And they sacrificed their sons, and their daughters to devils.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.105.38",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:38",
      "text": "And they shed innocent blood: the blood of their sons and of their daughters which they sacrificed to the idols of Chanaan. And the land was polluted with blood,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.105.39",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:39",
      "text": "And was defiled with their works: and they went aside after their own inventions.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.105.40",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:40",
      "text": "And the Lord was exceedingly angry with his people: and he abhorred his inheritance.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.105.41",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:41",
      "text": "And he delivered them into the hands of the nations: and they that hated them had dominion over them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.105.42",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 42,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:42",
      "text": "And their enemies afflicted them: and they were humbled under their hands:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.105.43",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 43,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:43",
      "text": "Many times did he deliver them. But they provoked him with their counsel: and they were brought low by their iniquities.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.105.44",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 44,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:44",
      "text": "And he saw when they were in tribulation: and he heard their prayer.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.105.45",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 45,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:45",
      "text": "And he was mindful of his covenant: and repented according to the multitude of his mercies.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.105.46",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 46,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:46",
      "text": "And he gave them unto mercies, in the sight of all those that had made them captives.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.105.47",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 47,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:47",
      "text": "Save us, O Lord, our God: and gather us from among the nations: That we may give thanks to thy holy name, and may glory in thy praise.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.105.48",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 48,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:48",
      "text": "Blessed be the Lord the God of Israel, from everlasting to everlasting: and let all the people say: So be it, so be it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
